<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8372&amp;p=87895#p87895"><![CDATA[
HuCard, the cartridge used in a TG16, is a miniaturized cartridge, not unlike a Game Boy cartridge. HU card (note the capitalization and spacing) was a smart card used to translate DirecTV key streams for a particular subscriber, long since obsoleted by the P4 and later D2 cards.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Dec 23, 2011 5:52 pm</p><hr />
