<title type="html"><![CDATA[Crisis Force and Summer Carnival '92 - Recca]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8372&amp;p=87381#p87381"><![CDATA[
Simple. As the 1st console in the world equipped with a CD-ROM XA simply wasn't available, also while it did have an ADPCM channel it's just a single mono channel and normally not meant to reproduce audio in high enough sample rate used for streamed music. Furthermore, the channel was already used in voices and data seeks on the 1X drive probably won't work well for "real-time streaming" events. Remember, the PCE was a console released in the late late 80's.<br /><br />Even for the PS1, a number of games (especially arcade conversions of fighting games) had animation cut to ensure smooth gameplay.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4653">Gilbert</a> — Mon Dec 12, 2011 6:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
